            "id": "4580485",
            "title": "Corning Non-GAAP EPS of $0.70 beats by $0.01, revenue of $4.35B beats by $40M",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>Corning <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20489853-corning-announces-strong-first-quarter-2026-financial-results-1\">press release</a> (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GLW\" title=\"Corning Incorporated\">GLW</a></span>): Q1 Non-GAAP EPS of $0.70 <span> beats by $0.01</span>.</li>\n<li>Revenue of $4.35B <span> beats by $40M</span>.</li>\n<li>Robust demand for Gen AI products and the ramp of new solar products drove Q1 growth.</li>\n<li>Optical Communications sales grew 36%, and Solar sales were up 80% year over year.</li>\n<li>\n<p data-eci=\"true\">Second-Quarter 2026 Outlook:</p>\n<ul><li>For the second quarter, management expects to grow core sales about 14% year over year to approximately $4.6 billion and core EPS about 25% year over year to a range of $0.73-$0.77.</li></ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
