            "id": "4580483",
            "title": "Xylem beats top-line and bottom-line estimates; updates FY26 revenue outlook",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>Xylem <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20489730-xylem-reports-first-quarter-results\">press release</a>  (XYL): Q1  Non-GAAP EPS of $1.12 <font color=\"green\"> beats by $0.04</font>.</li>\n<li>Revenue of $2.13B (+2.9% Y/Y) <font color=\"green\"> beats by $20M</font>.</li>\n<li>First-quarter adjusted earnings before interest, tax, depreciation, and amortization (EBITDA) margin was 20.6 percent, reflecting a year-over-year increase of 20 basis points.</li>\n<li>\n<p data-eci=\"true\"><strong>Outlook</strong></p>\n<p>Xylem now forecasts full-year 2026 revenue of approximately $9.2 to $9.3 billion <strong>vs. $9.19B consensus (prior $9.1 to $9.2 billion)</strong>, up approximately 2 to 3 percent on a reported basis, versus 1 to 3 percent previously guided, and up approximately 2 to 4 percent on an organic basis, as previously guided.</p>\n<p>Full-year 2026 adjusted EBITDA margin is expected to be approximately 22.9 to 23.3 percent, an increase of 70 to 110 basis points from Xylem’s 2025 adjusted results. This results in full-year adjusted earnings per share of $5.35 to $5.60 <strong>vs. $5.49 consensus  (prior</strong><strong> $5.35 to $5.60)</strong>, in line with the previous guidance range. Full-year free cash flow margin is still expected to be approximately 10.2 to 11.0 percent.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
            "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/news/4580483-xylem-beats-top-line-and-bottom-line-estimates-updates-fy26-revenue-outlook",
